David Light from The Data Partnership revealed the underhand tactics used by his company to coax information from people . 
  He admitted ignoring an official no-call list meant to protect the vulnerable . 
  Undercover reporter met Mr Light who has a 60-seater call centre in the Philippines and calls hundreds of thousands in Britain every month . 
  He offered to sell personal information from lifestyle surveys completed by people who had been cold-called from overseas . 
  He said they start with warm questions before going into financial details . 
 